Language.Sentence:
The Object view type produces an object that outputs the data in the form of specified information blocks, called items. This type works together with the VDOM package top-level container and the VDOM class object. The Object view objects displayes the items, while their appearance is set by the VDOM class object located in the VDOM package top-level container.
Before using the Object view type, create a new VDOM package top-level container and place a VDOM class object in it. Then place the Object view object on the web page where you want to display the items. In the 'VDOM class' attribute of the Object view object select the VDOM class to use. The 'Data' attribute of the Object view object specifies the data used in the items of the Object view object and can be formed dynamically by modifying it from the script. The data there must be written in the following format:
{
  "1": "{'city': 'Tomsk', 'zip': '634041', 'phone': '64-02-12'}",
  "2": "{'city': 'Sofia', 'zip': '1000', 'phone': '943 31 54'}" 
}

The way of items disposition inside the object:
horizontal - the item width does not change, they are disposed across the whole width of the Object view;
vertical - the items are disposed vertically without changing their width;
vertical wide - the  items are disposed vertically, their width is stretched to the Object view object's boundaries.

The overflow control mode:
Auto - if the content fits in the object' borders - scrolling will not be shown; if not - the scrolling will be shown;
Hidden - if the content does not fit in the object' borders - it will be cropped within the borders;
Scroll - the horizontal and vertical scrolling will always be shown, no matter if the content fits or not;
Visible - the whole content will always be shown without reference to the object's borders.

